  "title": "Service Technician",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities:</p><p>•\tPerform routine maintenance and inspection of security systems and equipment</p><p>•\tTroubleshoot, diagnose, and repair system faults (CCTV, access control, alarm systems, etc.)</p><p>•\tCarry out installation, testing, and commissioning of security systems when required</p><p>•\tRespond to service calls and emergency breakdowns, including rotating standby/on-call duties</p><p>•\tConduct system testing and ensure equipment is fully operational after repairs</p><p>•\tMaintain accurate service reports and maintenance records</p><p>•\tCoordinate with clients and site personnel during service activities</p><p>•\tEnsure compliance with safety standards and company procedures</p><p>•\tTravel frequently between client sites to perform assigned duties<br /></p><p>Requirements:</p><p>•\tTechnical qualification in Electronics, Electrical, IT, or related field</p><p>•\tExperience in servicing and maintaining security systems</p><p>•\tStrong hands-on troubleshooting and problem-solving skills</p><p>•\tKnowledge of IP networking and system configuration will be advantageous</p><p>•\tWillingness to work rotating standby schedules</p><p>•\tValid driver’s license and ability to travel within Singapore</p><p>•\tGood communication and customer service skills</p><p></p>",
